Class Car

  • java.lang.Object
    • component.Car

  • public class Car
extends java.lang.Object
    Models a Car object and its members/methods for traveling on roads from a starting to a stopping destination.
    Version:
    3.0
    Author:
    Reid Stagemeyer

      • move

        public void move(Tile[][] layout)
        The move method is called on car objects at every increment 'tick'. Updates the current state/speed of the car and its tile position/increment.
        Parameters:
        layout - current map layout

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Changes car's current state to 'stopped' which is used to indicate to delay for 1/2 second before beginning to move. Also sets current speed to 0.

      • waiting

        public void waiting()
        Changes current car's state to 'waiting' for waiting at an intersection. Also sets current speed to 0.

      • checkTile

        public boolean checkTile(Point nextTile,
                         Tile[][] layout)
        Checks the next Tile Point position on the current map layout and returns a boolean of 'true' if the tile is a valid one to move too.
        Parameters:
        nextTile - the car's next proposed position to check
        layout - the current map Tile layout
        Returns:
        'true' if valid, otherwise 'false'
